03:32:14.493 --> 03:32:16.933
Another thing that you might end up wanting to do

03:32:16.933 --> 03:32:21.933
is writing essentially a unit test for your application.

03:32:23.613 --> 03:32:25.853
One thing that you can do is

03:32:25.853 --> 03:32:30.053
instead of writing a unit test for your Shiny application,

03:32:30.053 --> 03:32:33.534
if you have a function that does a calculation,

03:32:33.534 --> 03:32:38.534
do the Python packaging technique

03:32:41.733 --> 03:32:44.293
of writing a unit test for that particular function.

03:32:44.293 --> 03:32:46.334
You can totally do that outside of Shiny.

03:32:46.334 --> 03:32:48.493
That is nothing special to Shiny itself.

03:32:48.493 --> 03:32:51.813
