03:33:46.774 --> 03:33:48.613
just to interact with,

03:33:51.134 --> 03:33:55.094
interact with a web browser through Python.

03:33:55.094 --> 03:33:56.973
It's in some sense similar to Selenium,

03:33:56.973 --> 03:33:58.493
except it's like the more modern way

03:33:58.493 --> 03:34:03.053
that you would be interacting with a website.

03:34:03.053 --> 03:34:05.053
And so if you have a Shiny app,

03:34:05.053 --> 03:34:07.694
the way you would work and test your Shiny app is,

03:34:07.694 --> 03:34:09.454
you first create the actual Shiny app

