or can these API calls get mixed?

03:38:37.213 --> 03:38:40.733
So there's actually parts of the Shiny API

03:38:40.733 --> 03:38:43.414
that are kind of intentionally,

03:38:44.654 --> 03:38:48.453
kind of power both of the modes.

03:38:48.453 --> 03:38:52.373
So if you look at say an Express app,

03:38:52.373 --> 03:38:56.534
you'll notice probably there's an import

03:38:56.534 --> 03:39:00.493
that looks like shiny.express import UI.

03:39:00.493 --> 03:39:03.054
That means that this namespace

03:39:03.054 --> 03:39:05.054
