03:39:12.733 --> 03:39:16.294
is designed to work just for Express.

03:39:16.294 --> 03:39:17.733
But even an Express app,

03:39:17.733 --> 03:39:22.733
you might see imports kind of from the top level of Shiny.

03:39:22.733 --> 03:39:24.014
So a lot of Express apps,

03:39:24.014 --> 03:39:28.453
you'll also see something like from Shiny import reactive.

03:39:28.453 --> 03:39:33.014
And that's kind of a signal that this thing that I'm,

03:39:33.014 --> 03:39:35.774
you know, importing from the top level of Shiny

03:39:35.774 --> 03:39:38.453
actually works the same way,

03:39:38.453 --> 03:39:42.573
regardless of whether you're in core or Express mode.

