03:51:05.593 --> 03:51:08.794
Okay, so you guys saw Playwright, right?

03:51:08.794 --> 03:51:10.794
Daniel demonstrated Playwright.

03:51:10.794 --> 03:51:14.274
So it is also, I think, a really good idea

03:51:14.274 --> 03:51:15.713
that when you're building a Shiny app

03:51:15.713 --> 03:51:19.274
to extract out all of the logic

03:51:19.274 --> 03:51:24.034
that is not Shiny-specific or Shiny-related.

03:51:24.034 --> 03:51:26.353
So if there are complicated transformations

03:51:26.353 --> 03:51:27.514
that you're doing to your data,

03:51:27.514 --> 03:51:30.953
if there are complicated plots that you need to create,

03:51:30.953 --> 03:51:35.193
if there are models that you need to load and apply,

03:51:35.193 --> 03:51:40.193
consider making a separate module, a separate .py file,

03:51:40.233 --> 03:51:41.973
and put all of your functions in there,

03:51:41.973 --> 03:51:45.554
and just have them take things like data frames as input,

03:51:45.554 --> 03:51:48.373
have them take variables as input.

03:51:48.373 --> 03:51:51.674
That way, you can test them entirely separate

03:51:51.674 --> 03:51:53.514
from your Shiny app.

03:51:53.514 --> 03:51:57.993
So your Shiny app.py becomes mostly UI

03:51:57.993 --> 03:52:02.993
and things that hook up UI to calls to these functions.

03:52:03.274 --> 03:52:05.514
Therefore, you can test the functions in isolation.

03:52:05.514 --> 03:52:06.453
That makes it much easier.

03:52:06.453 --> 03:52:08.674
You can test them interactively from a Jupyter Notebook

03:52:08.674 --> 03:52:10.934
or from the IPython console.

03:52:10.934 --> 03:52:13.193
So you can work much more quickly and iteratively.

03:52:13.193 --> 03:52:15.554
You can use the Python debugger.

03:52:15.554 --> 03:52:17.914
And if you really want to,

03:52:17.914 --> 03:52:20.353
you can also write a suite of unit tests

03:52:20.353 --> 03:52:22.754
using the PyTest framework.

03:52:23.754 --> 03:52:28.394
As far as testing it once it is inside of an application,

03:52:28.394 --> 03:52:30.674
then, and testing it from end to end,

03:52:30.674 --> 03:52:32.953
including all the Shiny code,

03:52:32.953 --> 03:52:35.993
yeah, Playwright is the way to go.

