04:00:23.914 --> 04:00:28.674
backwards because for all the things that Shiny does well, surely pointing and clicking

04:00:28.674 --> 04:00:35.313
your way through a Tableau dashboard, that's got to be easier and faster than writing Python

04:00:35.313 --> 04:00:42.313
code or R code. And he made a couple of points. He said, number one, that might be true the

04:00:42.553 --> 04:00:49.553
first time. But if you're making a bunch of similar BI dashboards that vary only in a

04:00:50.674 --> 04:00:55.354
few key ways, for a lot of these BI platforms that you're pointing and clicking your way

04:00:55.354 --> 04:01:02.354
through designing these dashboards, the ability to reuse logic, the ability to reuse building

04:01:03.194 --> 04:01:10.194
blocks that you've done before is very difficult. Even the ability to do exactly the same visualizations

04:01:10.553 --> 04:01:14.873
but now you have a totally different data set that you're using. It's like, all right,

04:01:14.873 --> 04:01:21.873
new dashboard or whatever. So that was one aspect of it. And then a second one was that

04:01:23.553 --> 04:01:29.913
when you're on your 10th BI dashboard, it's just not that fun anymore when you're pointing

04:01:29.913 --> 04:01:35.194
and clicking your way through. Whereas with Shiny, the more you do it, the faster you

04:01:35.194 --> 04:01:40.594
get. And then the third, which is a little bit cynical, but the third was it just felt

04:01:40.594 --> 04:01:46.974
like being able to do these things in code felt like a leveling up professionally in

04:01:46.974 --> 04:01:53.974
a way that I made another Power BI dashboard didn't. That being said, I think less cynically,

04:01:56.394 --> 04:02:02.673
there are frequently, I'm told there are frequently things that you want from your BI dashboard

04:02:02.673 --> 04:02:09.673
where Power BI can do 98% of it. But then that one last thing you can't do, you completely

04:02:10.433 --> 04:02:17.433
have to switch to another system. For example, you're using a dashboard to look at live-ish

04:02:17.753 --> 04:02:24.753
metrics and you're looking for outliers. Outliers in response time, outliers in inventory levels,

04:02:25.074 --> 04:02:30.634
whatever it is. And then when you see something, what happens? And with a Shiny dashboard,

04:02:30.634 --> 04:02:33.474
you might be able to say, it'd be really convenient if right here while I'm looking

04:02:33.474 --> 04:02:37.753
